<TITLE> RAB sues 2 Huji leaders for links to seized grenades </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com)The Rapid Action Battalion filed a case Saturday against Mufti Mainuddin Sheikh, alias Abu Jandal, and accomplice Nazrul Islam Ghorami in connection with over 40 grenades recovered in Satkhira the previous day. Khulna RAB-6 sub inspector KM Tariqul Islam filed the case with Debhata police against Jandal and Ghorami under the Explosives Act. Both are senior figures of banned Islamist outfit Harkatul Jihad. Jandal is known as second in command after Mufti Hannan. Satkhira police super Mirza Abdullahel Baki told bdnews24.com that a RAB team brought the two to Satkhira from Dhaka, arriving at 11.45 pm Saturday. The case was filed immediately on their arrival. They were handed to police in Debhata, Satkhira, where the grenades were recovered. The Rapid Action Battalion said in a press conference earlier Saturday that the 41 grenades recovered in Debhata Friday night were identical to the grenades launched at an Awami League rally on Aug 21, 2004. "The grenades we recovered are identical with the grenades of August 21," RAB director general Hasan Mahmud Khandaker told the press briefing. The militant group Harkatul Jihad, or Hujito which the two accused belonghas been accused of carrying out the Aug 21 grenade attack targeting Sheikh Hasina during an AL rally in 2004. Party secretary Ivy Rahman was among those who died in the attack. However, the Satkhira grenades were of recent manufacture, Khandaker said. The two accused were earlier brought to Dhaka following their arrests in connection to the recovered grenades, police and RAB officials said. After his arrest on Feb 14 in Gazipur, Abu Jandal was intensively quizzed. Based on information from Jandal, RAB recovered the grenades Friday at Shimulia village in Debhata, Satkhira. The elite force also arrested Nazrul Islam Ghorami, a resident of the village, in connection with the recovered grenades as they were kept in a pond nearby his house. Huji boss Mufti Hannan is now in jail. He is accused in several cases including one in connection with a grenade attack on British High Commissioner Anwar Choudhury. bdnews24.co
